column17: Other thoughts about your experience of Belmont:

Belmont is honestly the biggest social experiment for Christian’s, this “Christian school” isn’t Christian at all, profs aren’t Christian and most of them don’t understand the values of being a Christian and honestly it really is hard going here and also being a Christian, have and finding friends that are also Christian and trying to find groups with people are crazy hard and there is also no “campus life” it’s always so mopey and sad and there’s never anything going on
We need to get a bigger gym
Yolanda Benjamin Rita is coming for you bitches
I love it! Every place has its pros and cons but for me, the positives outweigh the negatives.
The people have really made the experience, teachers and students alike. I’m so lucky to have met so many great people already!

there are many rules for all of us being in college! everyone feels very babied even though we are all adults! the campus activities are also a little childish! i also wish there was more greek life options
